_:N0ae86c49623143c880419d8ab325a845 <http://schema.org/description> "<p>Chris McDonald MP was appointed Minister for Industry in the Department for Energy Security and Net Zero (<abbr title=\"Department for Energy Security and Net Zero\">DESNZ</abbr>) and the Department for Business and Trade (<abbr title=\"Department for Business and Trade\">DBT</abbr>) on 11 September 2025.</p>\n\n<p>He was elected as the MP for Stockton North in July 2024.</p>\n\n<h3 id=\"education\">Education</h3>\n\n<p>Chris studied Chemical Engineering at Cambridge, graduating with <abbr title=\"Bachelor of Arts\">BA</abbr> and <abbr title=\"Master of Engineering\">MEng</abbr> degrees. He also completed an <abbr title=\"Master of Business Administration\">MBA</abbr> at the University of Warwick.</p>\n\n<h3 id=\"career-outside-politics\">Career outside politics</h3>\n\n<p>Before becoming an MP Chris spent 20 years working in the steel industry, with a focus on research.</p>\n\n<p>In 2008, he became a laboratory manager within the research division of Tata Steel. In 2014 he led the divestment of the Materials Processing Institute from Tata Steel UK, becoming <abbr title=\"chief executive officer\">CEO</abbr>.</p>\n\n<p>Chris is also a Fellow at the Royal Academy of Engineering.</p>\n\n" .
